Fix: Notas showing gear icon in dock (GNOME/Wayland)


If Notas displays a generic gear icon instead of its proper icon in the dock, add the missing StartupWMClass to the desktop file:

edit this:
nano /usr/share/applications/notas.desktop

replace with:

```[Desktop Entry]
Name=Notas
GenericName=Encrypted Notes
Comment=Secure encrypted notes application
Exec=notas
Icon=/usr/share/icons/hicolor/256x256/apps/notas.png
Terminal=false
Type=Application
Categories=Utility;TextEditor;Security;
Keywords=notes;encrypted;secure;private;
StartupNotify=true
StartupWMClass=com.jegly.Notas
```

Update the desktop database:
update-desktop-database /usr/share/applications/

Restart Notas and the correct icon should now appear in the dock.
